            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "In every aspect SV high school meets my expectation and my child loves to go school even on holidays. But now the table has turned.\n\nLast 1 week my child refuse to go school when I asked the reason he scared of  his PET mam. He says his PET mam is scolding and threatens to beat. Cross checked with 2 of my child classmates. Both complains the same. She Speaks Rude with parents too at times. That's Bit annoying attitude while pick up drop off.\n\nI thought of bringing this to principal, but I believe management knows this well they encourage  this attitude to control students.\nI will be transferring my child to another school if this persist",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
